    <item>
      <title>Bitwarden SSH Agent on Fedora Workstation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/bitwarden-ssh-agent/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 27 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/bitwarden-ssh-agent/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;bitwarden-ssh-agent-on-fedora-workstation&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Bitwarden SSH Agent on Fedora Workstation&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#bitwarden-ssh-agent-on-fedora-workstation&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequistes&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Prerequistes&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#prerequistes&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bitwarden Desktop Application in our case flatpak version&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bitwarden SSH Agent Enabled&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Public Key deployed to the target server&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;steps&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Steps&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#steps&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;make-sure-the-bitwarden-is-running-and-ssh-agent-is-active&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Make Sure the Bitwarden is running and SSH Agent is Active&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#make-sure-the-bitwarden-is-running-and-ssh-agent-is-active&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Open your Bitwarden desktop application.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Go to &lt;strong&gt;Settings&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Navigate to the &lt;strong&gt;SSH Agent&lt;/strong&gt; section.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Confirm that the &lt;strong&gt;Enable SSH Agent&lt;/strong&gt; option is checked.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;configure-our-environement-to-use-the-agent&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Configure Our Environement to use the Agent&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#configure-our-environement-to-use-the-agent&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint info&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;For this step you need to identify the Socket Path this path will vary depending on how you installed the bitwarden client. In this case we are using the **Flatpak** version.&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;execute-the-following-in-a-terminal-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Execute the following in a terminal shell:&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#execute-the-following-in-a-terminal-shell&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;export SSH_AUTH_SOCK&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;~/.var/app/com.bitwarden.desktop/data/.bitwarden-ssh-agent.sock&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;connect-via-ssh-to-verify-the-agent-works&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Connect via SSH to verify the agent works:&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#connect-via-ssh-to-verify-the-agent-works&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt; ssh your_username@your_server_ip_or_hostname&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;set-the-variable-permenantly-in-bash-or-zshrc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Set the variable permenantly in bash or zshrc:&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#set-the-variable-permenantly-in-bash-or-zshrc&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open your shell configuration file (e.g., &lt;code&gt;nano ~/.bashrc&lt;/code&gt; for Bash, &lt;code&gt;nano ~/.zshrc&lt;/code&gt; for Zsh)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
